  "abstract": "The Department of the Treasury (Treasury) and the Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) are jointly issuing this interim rule pursuant to section 121 of the Gramm-Leach-Bliley Act (GLBA). The GLBA permits a national bank or state member bank that is among the second 50 largest insured banks to own or control a financial subsidiary only if the bank meets either the eligible debt requirement set forth in section 121 of the Act or alternative criteria established jointly by Treas",
